<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-10T09:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-10T09:30:00-05:00" n="1186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1186">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/3</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-10T17:00:00+02:30">
                                <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 11, 7:15 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>11. Condition of Austrian’s and Germans arrested as prisoners of war and
                            sent to interior very bad. According to advices from all sources,
                            Government has done almost nothing to house and feed them properly,
                            resulting in suffering and sickness. If something is not done soon
                            before cold weather, conditions will become fearful. Am protesting daily
                            at Foreign Office concerning this matter; improvement and investigation
                            promised but conditions unchanged. As Russia desires greatly to securer
                            favorable opinion of America, word to Russian Ambassador this matter
                            might have good effect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <pb facs="1065" n="751" xml:id="pg_751"/>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WCS1"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Telegram]</note>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>11. Your August 26, 6 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d1186fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> and No. 11, September 10, 5 p.m. As no
                                instructions seem to have been sent to you, please explain as to
                                protests and discontinue same until otherwise instructed.</p>
                            <p rend="right">
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </p>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>